< Review>
They take cash and card, a good selection of tires the used tires they sell are good quality and the new tires prices are very good I got four new tires for $260 and the guy installed them quickly. They don't have an alignment machine but I'm sure they send you to another location for that if you ask. The place is a little small and gets busy so plan for that. They are very friendly people they do a good job. Please don't be a n a hole  tip the guys working on your car they really appreciate it.<//Review>

< review>
I'm editing this review after I spoke with Jerry on the phone. Originally I had a negative review as my wheels were not treated with the proper car they should've. From being out of balance, to scratches, to missing my valve stem caps, I was not too happy with the service especially because I trusted them in the past. Jerry was extremely quick to reach out to my review and make things right. He assured me he will stay on top of his employees and make sure my experience doesn't happen to anyone else. Strictly for how passionate and helpful Jerry was, I'm coming back to rewrite my thoughts that people make mistakes, and although some are much worse then others, what's important is that things can be made right, which in this case definitely did. This tire shop has won back my service as there customer service was above all else. Thank you!< /review>

<Text>I absolutely hate acrylics but my natural nails broke and I had an event to go to. I came here to get them done and the lady did an okay job. I requested almond shape and she did them oval. I tried to tell her that I wanted the tips slightly more pointed and she raised her voice at me saying she did almond shape like I asked. The acrylic close to my cuticles were very clumpy and not smooth. Even with all that, I would have given them 3 stars, buuuuut....
I made the mistake of coming back here to have the acrylics removed after the event. My natural nails had a decent length (1/8 inch past fingertips) so I asked to have the acrylics removed and get a gel polish manicure. Well the woman grinded off the thickness of the nails as I expected, then started tearing off the rest! LAYERS of my natural nails came off with the acrylics and it was very painful as I expressed throughout the service. I asked why not soak them in a solution to soften it first and she said they don't do that. Needless to say, I had NO natural nails left! The entire length is gone and they are paper thin. Not to mention throbbing!!! I understand acrylics will weaken nails but this was too much. I could have removed them like this at home, but I went to a professional establishment so there would be as little damage as possible. The gel polish was also done very poorly. I chose a light natural pink color since I did not want to bring attention to the nubs that are now left on my fingertips. The polish is all over my cuticles and even the sides of my fingers.  Oh, and I forgot to mention, the manicure water I soaked my hands is was ice cold (which with the throbbing was actually soothing, but not acceptable for normal manicure). When she was finally done I mentioned to the lady at the front that I was not happy, in pain and very unpleased with the service provided. She said nothing was done wrong but she gave me a whopping $3 off to compensate.
Do yourself a favor and save your nails by going somewhere else.</Text></record></dataset><record>

<Name>Marsha Dudik< /Name><date>1560995450746<//date><Rate>5< /Rate>< Review>
This hotel has all the charm of a California 60's hotel with the bonus of updated amenities!

We were treated to a kitchen suite with a full-sized refrigerator and gas stove/oven. The room was spacious and the bathroom was better than most 4 star hotels with beautiful new tile work.

Though on a busy street, the room was quiet. Housekeeping was outstanding and the room was very clean. The manager was very attentive and helpful.

A major drawback to our vacation was our dog getting hit by a car. Patrick (the manager) was amazing by helping her and then locating a vet hospital for us. He helped us arrange for a longer stay to accommodate for her surgery and continued to check on her daily.

A big thanks to everyone at Viking Motel!<//Review>

I arrived for check-in and they said that their website had cancelled my reservation even though I had the printout of my approved reservation. They sold me their 'last room' for an extra $40- I was stuck. The room was great with a nice shower, kitchen and comfortable bed. My tv remote had no batteries so I asked for some. They couldn't find any. I was going out anyway so asked that they put the remote back in the room once they found the batteries. Several hours later there was still no remote. I finally rang their bell at 8am the next day and asked for the remote back so that I could just go buy some batteries myself. They found the batteries. The couple was very nice and the room was nice, but my situation was certainly not handled properly.< /review>

<name>Expedia reviewer</name><Date>1432857600000< /Date>< rating>
None<//rating>
< Review>
So, on a normal day, I cant say I would recommend this motel over other hotels. Here are the pros: clean, lots of space, kitchen area with full fridge, nice TV, there is a woman at the front office who is very friendly, it is super close to the CLIF Bar Mountains to Beach race location. Here are the cons: very outdated, room smelled like smoke when not aired, there is a man at the front office who is not the most friendly, motel is not really in a great location if you dont have a car. When I say outdated, I mean, it definitely needs an overhaul. I pulled back the comforter on the bed and immediately saw two holes from cigarette burns on the underside of the comforter, but they obviously just used it anyway. Its a fine place for necessity but I wouldnt choose it over a nicer hotel for the price of one was coming for a longer vacation.</Review>

< Text>
I have nothing but great things to say about my recent Taycan leasing experience with Sales Ambassador Gilbert Villagrana and Finance Ambassador Shelly Fisher III.  Both were ultra professional and helpful at every stage.  I emailed the dealership about a Taycan 4S that had just arrived, and heard back from Gilbert the same day, with a video of the car.  The next day we negotiated a very competitive lease price, and I put down a deposit to hold the car.  I then discovered I needed a bigger battery and asked Gilbert to find me a different 4S, in a hard-to-find color, with other desired options.  Diring the next two weeks he scoured all available and incoming inventory at dealerships throughout Ca and neighboring states, keeping me posted along the way.  Eventually Gilbert found just the right car coming into another dealership.

Even though Porsche Ontario needed to swap a car with a dealership hundreds of miles away to get me the one I wanted, they honored the original price we had negotiated for a car in their inventory.  The day after I signed the lease, Gilbert drove 6 hours to pick up my car at the other dealership, dropped his own car off, and then drove my car another 3 hours further to deliver it to my home.  I told him he didn't need to do that, but Gilbert wanted to configure the PCM and other systems, explain the car's features, and answer any questions I might have.  He then Ubered back to the other dealership to pick up his own car and return home.  All on a Friday!  During the next week Gilbert checked in regularly and helped answer my follow-up questions.  The Taycan is a complicated car and this proved very helpful.  How's that for going the extra mile?

Shelly was also great to deal with.  I've come to dread the usual finance department add-on pitches and hard sells.  That's not what I encountered with Shelly.  He explained the add-on packages that Porsche makes available, made straightforward recommendations about what he thought made sense for a lessee, and completely left it to me to decide with no pressure whatsoever.  Shelly also arranged for me to docu-sign all the papers and expedited completion of my lease.

I'm an attorney, I dislike surprises, and I know when someone is trying to game me. I encountered none of that.  On the contrary, I have never had a better car buying/leasing experience with any brand or dealership.   Not even close.   These gentlemen are the best, bar none.  I would do business again with either of them, and with the Porsche Ontario dealership, in a flash.

As for the Taycan 4S, it's a high spirited thing of beauty.  I  have never driven anything quite like this solid rocket. After blast off, you can just sit back and enjoy the sound system, which also delivers the best acoustic experience I've ever had.   Nice work Porsche.  Now I'm thinking 12k/year will not be enough.<//Text>

<rate>5</rate>< Text>
I recently Purchased a new Panamera 4 for my wife. We traded in her Mercedes Benz. My experience was actually very good. We arrived at the dealer and was greeted by Megan Breunig. A very nice young lady who took us on the test drive. She was very knowledgeable about the vehicle, and very personable. I fully expected her to pass us off to another Sales person or Manager after the test drive, but it never happened. Nice thing about the dealership was I dealt with Megan start to finish. It was nice to deal with one person start to finish, that usually never happens. We worked on the numbers of the new car which was fairly straight forward, as the dealership had the vehicle I was interested in priced very fair to begin with. Where I usually have the issue is with the trade in. That is when things generally go south. They offered me from the beginning, what I felt was a very fair price for my trade in. I had already done my research so I knew what a fair offer was, and what I would accept. We made some minor adjustments on the numbers came to an agreement and my wife drove home the car of her dreams. It was really just that simple! The entire staff was awesome but Megan went the extra mile and never once pressured me. She listened to my concerns, work for me to make sure I was happy with my purchase and that I was completely satisfied. After the paperwork was complete it was time to take delivery.  Megan made sure my wife knew everything about her new car. She took her time explaining everything, how it works, set up her phone, and I could not have been  more pleased. Usually there is a quick once over and they send you on your way. Then its up to me to figure out the car and explain it all to my wife. It was by all accounts, a very good experience start to finish. Cannot say enough about Megan and the staff at Porsche Ontario. Our sincere thanks!

Raymond and Nancy Gutierrez</Text>

< text>
If you go in here, there are two options for you specialty pizza and build your own. Well, I'm a small eater, so I chose build your own and picked small size. Small size came with 4 slices which was more than enough to fill my portion and then some. It was really delicious and what was even better was that the dining room was very spacy and cozy. They had some christmas decorations and lighting was just bright enough for good moody brightness.</text>

< review>
This place is a minor part of the myth and legend of rock climbing in the valley so I hate to leave it a negative review but it is bad. There was an extremely long wait to order and to get food, the breadsticks were burned, the pizza was no better than frozen, and the employees clearly didn't care at all with one working while the other two watched or fooled around with the kitchen gear and food. There was garbage on all the tables and on the ground with no one cleaning it up. The raccoons can be entertaining or annoying depending on whether or not they stay under your table or climb onto it. This restaurant is a great example of what happens when there is no competition.</review>

<Date>1572741033796</Date>< review>
Tom's Jr. was great! They did not disappoint! I always get a pastrami combo! It's tasty until the last bite. I add their fresh, crisp chili peppers for a little kick, but they are certainly not necessary to enjoy the pastrami! I got a steak sandwich (meat only), too. They serve a nice - sized rib eye steak, so tender that you don't need a knife.  I will say that back in the day, their pastrami sandwiches were so big you'd have enough left over for a lunch or meal the next day! That included the huge-sized fries. Today,  that's not the case because they keep their prices affordable, so, it's a win-win for everybody! For me, I choose quality over quantity - any day! I recommend this location as, well! It was very clean and modern! Many people were eating in and driving through! I look forward to my next visit!<//review>

< text>
Used to be a fairly satisfactory burgers and salads place for walking distance commuters,  but when one has a car, there are better, more enticing fast food places.  But, this location is lacking on 2 main FRONTS,  customer courtesy and food quality.  Ordered a chicken salad but it was rather a letuce and tomatoe salad, drive though lady almost forgot my ranch dressing (FIRST STRIKE) but luckily I did not press the  ccelerator and drove off from Drivethrough,  (STRIKE 2) upon request I Demanded  my dressing.  Dressing container was too small considering I had ordered a salad.  Requested an additional but  additional would cost an dditional price. (STRIKE 3)  MY IMPRESSION: lady  dispatching treats customers more as ghettoo recipients than customer .    Well anyways, I
parked to the curb  to eat my salad, turns out that dressing was deluted...why would I continue going  to Tom's Jr.  When we have Johnson Brother 's   BBQ a  block away, subway,  a quarter of a mile away or the Habit for a salad specialty On alondra and paramount Blvd.?  This Tom's  Jr. location was a disappointment.< /text>

Great food and nice dining or breakfast experience!!!

The menu it's assertive and easy to read, the clerks greet you and help you to make your food selection.
The dining area it's really clean and it has big tables, the soda fountain has a good variety of drinks and they have refills.

Great sense of security, since cops tend to have breakfast, lunch or dinner 24/7.<//review>
